<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="86" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[1290,2275,1738,2790]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86">Description. Shell very small, high-spired with many whorls, thin, anomphalous. Protoconch of about 1Y2 smooth whorls, flattened top with strongly arched whorl profile; the transition from protoconch to teleoconch sharp and gently sinuated. Teleoconch of 7Y2 smooth whorls, whorl profile arched, suture moderately deep, deeper in neanic stage; length of whorl gradually increased with growth. Aperture D-shaped; inner lip almost straight, broad anterior notch, columellar fold obscured, parietal inductura thin; outer lip straight, strong prosocline; base pointed.</paragraph>
